Changelog
=========

0.7.8 - sáb dic 13 11:14:35 CET 2003
------------------------------------

 - Massive cleaning to double screen dumping code.
 - Double modes use the scale2x algorithm.
 - Big sounds work in Linux.
 - Many bugfixes.

0.7.7 - dom abr  7 17:20:30 CEST 2002
-------------------------------------

 - A new accumulation buffer.

 - New variable _qdgdfv_gamma_correct, to apply gamma correction.

 - A new antialiased double mode, controlled by the
   _qdgdfv_double_antialias variable.

0.7.6 - dom feb 24 09:17:48 CET 2002
------------------------------------

 - Support for esound (enlightened sound daemon) in qdgdf_audio
   (compilable using AUDIO=ESD).

 - New key variables for the function keys.

 - Bug fixed in the font charset encoding conversion.

0.7.5 - dom feb  3 18:25:37 CET 2002
------------------------------------

 - New color blending code.

 - New support for loading big sound files.

0.7.4 - jue ene 10 16:50:37 CET 2002
------------------------------------

 - qdgdfa_play_sound() semantics has been unified between
   platforms; a request to play a sound that is already
   playing does nothing in all platforms.

 - New qdgdfa_respawn_sound() function, to play a sound
   that may be already playing.

 - New qdgdfa_dup_sound() function, to duplicate a sound.

 - It's no longer necessary to fill the _qdgdfa_window_title[]
   string in win32 (in Linux it was never mandatory), as a valid
   window handler is obtained by other ways. Anyway, it can
   still be used.

 - Some scancode fixings (win32).

0.7.3 - dom nov 18 22:09:27 CET 2001
------------------------------------

 - Improved documentation.

 - New qdgdfv_build_light_table_ext() function.

 - More resolution timer using gettimeofday().

0.7.2 - jue oct 11 21:14:59 CEST 2001
-------------------------------------

 - New qdgdfv_timer() function.

 - New qdgdfv_build_light_table() function.

